                            <comment id="13740053" author="vrodionov" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 19:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Having ability to control custom table/CF attributes through HBase shell is a nice feature to have (coprocessors can introduce custom attributes, for example). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13740096" author="stack" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2013 19:42:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm... I thought this worked.  Let me take look...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13741301" author="vrodionov" created="Thu, 15 Aug 2013 18:24:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is ruby stuff I am not familiar with. Can someone give me direction I will try to fix it myself. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13814645" author="rwang" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2013 06:09:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had the same problem when i trying to execute a &apos;alter&apos; command, here is the cmd:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;alter &apos;SPLIT_TEST_BIG&apos;, &lt;/p&gt;
{METHOD =&amp;gt; &apos;table_att&apos;, &apos;SPLIT_POLICY&apos; =&amp;gt; &apos;org.apache.hadoop.hbase.regionserver.ConstantSizeRegionSplitPolicy&apos;}

&lt;p&gt;The split policy is not changed for table &apos;SPLIT_TEST_BIG&apos;, by digging the code, i found HTableDescriptor.getRegionSplitPolicyClassName in method HRegion.initializeRegionInternals always returns null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The HBase i&apos;m using is 0.94.6-cdh4.4.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819576" author="stack" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 23:17:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Check good in 0.96 too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13824288" author="stack" created="Sat, 16 Nov 2013 00:48:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7571&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7571&lt;/a&gt; made this work in 0.96 and trunk.  This issue then becomes about backporting that fix or part of that fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13867418" author="lhofhansl" created="Fri, 10 Jan 2014 01:55:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Somebody make a patch, please.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893090" author="lhofhansl" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 06:12:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vmariyala&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vmariyala&quot;&gt;Vasu Mariyala&lt;/a&gt;, feel like looking into a patch for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893690" author="vasu.mariyala@gmail.com" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 19:24:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lhofhansl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lhofhansl&quot;&gt;Lars Hofhansl&lt;/a&gt; Started making the changes. Will upload the patch soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
